        "en": "What is it exactly? A molecular intervention for modulating reality perception and performance capability. Who is affected? The entire socioeconomic spectrum; from the optimized performance subject (microdosing) to the marginalized loser (sedation). Where is the epicenter? In the synaptic cleft (microscopically) and in the transatlantic logistics chains of narco-capitalism (macroscopically). When does it become critical? When the chemical prosthesis becomes the condition of possibility for social participation (addiction/dependence). Why is it happening now? Because the individual's psychic resilience can no longer keep pace with the acceleration of digital late capitalism. How can the system be stabilized? Through decriminalization, harm reduction, and decoupling of intoxication from criminal prosecution. From the perspective of systems theory (Luhmann), drug consumption is a risky self-irritation of the psychic system to manipulate the structural coupling to the organic system. The body is understood as a biochemical state space into which negentropy (order/energy) is artificially injected through exogenous ligands. This leads to a short-term increase in system complexity (high), but long-term accumulation of entropy (tolerance, toxicity, system crash). Thermodynamically considered, addiction is an energy deficit business: The effort to maintain homeostasis increases exponentially, while the external energy supply (dose) decreases linearly. Synthesis lowers fixed costs, cartel logics become more modular. Platforms and encrypted chats reduce physical trade risk. Harm-reduction programs stabilise mortality yet face moral pushback. Poly-drug use raises interactions while purity data stay opaque."
